{"title":"Suricata Event Guide","type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"These are the names of the Suricata events you should see in the Suricata Event Types Data Table:

| event_type | description                                                           |
|------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------|
| alert      | these are alerts created by a rule evaluating true                    |
| dns        | logs of DNS (domain name server) name lookup activiity                |
| fileinfo   |  information about files observed in network packets                  |
| flow       | logs of network activity by port and protocol                         |
| http       | logs of http (web) activity                                           |
| ssh        | logs of observed SSH (secure shell) traffic                           |
| stats      | performance metrics like dropped packets                              |
| tls        | logs of https (web) activity and observed certificates using TLS/ SSL |

If you do not see all six of these events in your live data table, some Suricata events may be missing or disabled. 

References:
- https://suricata.readthedocs.io/en/latest/output/eve/eve-json-output.html#
- https://resources.sei.cmu.edu/asset_files/Presentation/2016_017_001_449890.pdf

Configuration examples: 
- https://github.com/randomuserid/Tylium/tree/master/Suricata","openLinksInNewTab":false,"fontSize":10},"aggs":[]}

{"title":"Sysmon Event Guide","type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"Sysmon Event Guide

These are the names and IDs of the Sysmon events you should see in the Sysmon Event Types Data Table:

| event.code | event.action                                           |
|------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| 8          | CreateRemoteThread detected (rule: CreateRemoteThread) |
| 22         | Dns query (rule: DnsQuery)                             |
| 6          | Driver loaded (rule: DriverLoad)                       |
| 11         | File created (rule: FileCreate)                        |
| 2          | File creation time changed (rule: FileCreateTime)      |
| 15         | File stream created (rule: FileCreateStreamHash)       |
| 7          | Image loaded (rule: ImageLoad)                         |
| 3          | Network connection detected (rule: NetworkConnect)     |
| 1          | Process Create (rule: ProcessCreate)                   |
| 5          | Process terminated (rule: ProcessTerminate)            |
| 12         | Registry object added or deleted (rule: RegistryEvent) |
| 13         | Registry value set (rule: RegistryEvent)               |
| 4          | Sysmon service state changed                           |
| 20         | WmiEventConsumer activity detected                     |
| 21         | WmiEventConsumerToFilter activity detected             |
| 19         | WmiEventFilter activity detected                       |

If you do not see all sixteen of these events in your live data table, some Sysmon events may be missing or disabled.
